This week, Lionsgate held a tastemaker screening for the upcoming movie LA LA LAND at MoMaâ€™s (Museum of Modern Art) Titus Theater, hosted by Jennifer Lawrence. Damien Chazelle, Emma Stone, Benj Pasek, Justin Paul and Marc Platt were all in attendance. LA LA Land is a musical comedy drama starring Ryan Gosling and Emma Stone in the title role. The film is directed by Damien Chazelle, who previously helmed the film Whiplash. The film centres on an musician who falls for an aspiring actress in Los Angeles, with the title LA LA Land referring to the city of angels and how it is perceived to be out of touch with reality.